      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "The Nethinims, whom",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "David and the princes had appointed.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " We learn this fact from the present passage only; since neither in Kings nor Chronicles is there any mention made of David's adding to the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "hieroduli",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", or temple servants. It is, however, quite in accordance with his other arrangements that he should have done so. The original Nethinims were the Gibeonites (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Joshua 9:23",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "All...",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "  ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "were expressed by name.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " Iddo sent to Ezra a list of the Nethinims, which, however, he does not think it necessary to insert. ",
